                  <handDesc>
                     <p>Written along the fibers; the scribe rotated the papyrus 90 degrees; the text is partly abraded in some parts; the letters are of upright large-sized cursive; tachygraphical hand; characterized by long sloping letters; frequently invade the big interlinear space; upsilon is superscripted above the line; no diacritical marks.</p>
